social_posts.post_text: I’ll be in Antarctica with fam for a couple weeks. Taking a break from my podcast and social. If you were laying on your death bed, what are the things you wish you did? Those are the things you should be doing. 😉

The quicker you accept this, the quicker you will be on your way to meeting your person. Don’t wait around hoping someone will change. They might come around, they might not. In the meantime, move forward and take care of building the life you want. ❤️
I say this to people alllll the time. Getting what you want is actually easy when you are clear and know where to look.
If you want to know more about someone, observe their friends. ☺️
Had a great time at @character.media @unforgettablegala celebrating Asians in Entertainment! ❤️

If your career takes off, it means you are putting time into it, which means it is important to you. When you were in your last relationship, you were likely using your energy toward the other person in a way that wasn’t fully in alignment with yourself.
⠀
It’s not uncommon that a woman’s career will take off after a relationship ends. Example: Ariana Grande right before her 7 rings album. Ana de Armas post Ben Affleck (tbh I think she dodged a bullet). After their breakups they were on FIRE.🔥
⠀
Imagine yourself shining. How does your ideal partner look? Do they have a smile on their face? Are they excited for you? Do they offer to hold your purse while you’re on the red carpet? Do they stay home to watch the kids while rooting for you? WHAT DOES SUPPORT LOOK LIKE TO YOU?
⠀
A good relationship supports the full expressed version of you. The superstar version! 🌟
Everyone is responsible for how they show up in a relationship. Take responsibility for your part.
Merry Xmas! ❤️

Walks with ma.❤️ I found myself SUPER irritable the first few days visiting home. Same ol family stuff that can stack up and trigger us. Then I tried to remember that the world doesn’t revolve around me. 🤡
⠀
If you have a complicated relationship with your mom, don’t forget she is the reason you exist. She chose your dad, endured 9 months of growing you in her belly, and birthed your ass. She is why you get to be here.
⠀
Love you ma. I wonder where I learned to be such a stubborn rebellious biatch? 🐲❤️
Thanks for sponsoring the @unforgettablegala Lexus but you know us Asians would buy your cars regardless. 😂

Glad you are spiritually connected in the 5D and that he is a Scorpio with Leo rising, but homeboy is right infront of you and has no integrity. 🧐😂 When people get too “woo” (to the point that it is a disservice to their romantic life), I like to remind them what is infront of them. If you want to function in the 3D (aka on earth), you have to consider other things besides an energetic draw toward someone. 🙃 Clip from episode # 295 with @yurisinata. We talk about dating post divorce, toxic masculinity, and how previous partners shape what you prioritize in relationships. ❤️ #showupwithchristinechang

Two weeks away from the hubs and we’ve both been consumed with family stuff for the last 6 weeks. Life isn’t a 24/7 vacation with zero responsibilities. This is reality. Unexpected stuff comes up. Things may look different than you thought. Learning to accept and flow with life is one of the best skills to have. I usually master this right after the breakdown. 🫠😂
How’s your self-awareness? Are you doing exactly what you hate from the “other side?” 🧐 Clip from episode # 295 with @yurisinata. ❤️
Whichever it is, if there is a pattern, the only constant variable is you. 🙂
The modern woman is multi faceted. For a long time I believed I had to do and be one thing. Those days are over. ⚡️

Comedian @shiningluvsmile & I talk about growing up wealthy and how that can impact one’s values. 💰 I love this conversation because money is a healthy conversation topic that should be normalized. 🙌🏽 What are your values when it comes to money? Clip from episode # 296. #showupwithchristinechang

Rainy day reads.😌 This book by @neetabhushan comes at a perfect time as I’m going through challenges with family stuff and life transitions.
⠀
Labeling your emotions and where you are in the process is what we need to do if we want to know what the next step is. “That Sucked, Now What” gives a step-by-step framework into HOW to productively move through those sucky moments when you feel stuck on a damn hamster wheel.
⠀
My goal is always to move through life with grace and acceptance. Keep moving forward, even if it’s baby steps. ❤️
⠀
#ThatSuckedNowWhat
Home. 🏠

We say we want a lot of things, but do we really? 🤔 Remember that what you love about someone also includes the less-than-ideal things that generally come with it.
⠀
Example: Rich, successful, alpha guy. The qualities that make him what he is can also make him a particular person who is used to living life his way. Is that compatible with your personality and emotional needs?
⠀
Clip from episode # 296 with Comedian @shiningluvsmile.
⠀
#showupwithchristinechang

Each month I look at the deposits from my book sales on Amazon. I published my book, “Show Up: Finding Love for Independent Women” a couple years ago. Right now I call my book sales my “food money.”🙂🍔 I kind of spend a lot of money on food, so it’s not bad! Despite these deposits not being PHAT, they still make me happy. Why?
⠀
1. People who I don’t know continue to buy my book (with tbh, little promotion on my end). I knew dating was a topic that needed to be talked about more among high-performing women, because relationships were something I struggled with (like, a lot) when I was single and learning about myself. My book is a blue print to help single women gain confidence and clarity with their relationships. It’s something I wish I had when I was dating and in the dumpster fire of getting my heart shattered over and over.
⠀
2. These small but CONSISTENT deposits into my bank account add up over time, and will only snowball. From my experience, the businesses that grow consistently + gradually have the most success over time.
⠀
If you feel discouraged or disappointed, keep going. Have patience. If you are living your truth, trust that what you are doing is serving its purpose. ☺️

My first time at Sundance with @sunrisecollective.us! I am passionate about supporting fellow API (Asian Pacific Islander) creatives in media. I LOVE story telling, and what better stories to tell but our own? 🥰

If you want to thrive in life, you need to make peace with your upbringing. Everyone is doing the best they can with what they know. Do YOU get everything in life right?  Do YOU know everything? Is it possible for you to show some grace? 🧐
⠀
Clip from episode # 297 with @neetabhushan. We talk about growing up with immigrant parents and how to flow through life with more ease. Her new book “That Sucked Now What?” gives more detailed framework beyond our conversation, and hits bookshelves Jan 31st! 

#showupwithchristinechang #thatsuckednowwhat
Sundance dream team. @thisisge

Our nervous systems are out of whack from constant stimulation. Personally, I gain the most clarity when I take a break from DOING and CONSUMING. That’s when there’s ideas, creativity, and connection to source. Quiet down the noise. 😌 Clip from episode #295 with @yurisinata. #showupwithchristinechang

Happy book launch day to the hardest working woman I know! If you’ve ever written a book before, you know it’s like birthing a baby (+ she already has two kids under 4 at home). 🫠 I’ve learned so much from @neetabhushan, including how to have energy to do 180 podcast interviews within a month (hint: IV drips), + how to promote like crazy in order to have a killer launch. None of which I did when I published my book. Lol. Congrats @neetabhushan, to the moon. 🫶🏽🚀
⠀
That Sucked, Now What? is available for purchase on all main platforms where you buy yo books!
⠀
#thatsuckednowwhat #booklaunch
LIFE UPDATE. 😎
The smartest choice I’ve ever made.

Heal & Flow. Integrity. Truth.✨ Had a great weekend turning down the noise and getting centered with a group of people who truly lead by example.
⠀
I’m careful with the coaching/spiritual/healing industry because there are unfortunately some (a lot) of people who coach with a lack of morals, humility, and ultimately to serve only themselves.
⠀
@edsbritton & @bigjoe are the real deal. I highly recommend following them and attending any of their retreats. Integrity + truth are two of my core values and I’m happy to be attracting more people in my life who embody it. ❤️‍🔥 Thank you for organizing the weekend @beloved.body and thank you for the yummy food @kristen_noel__ !
Beginner hip hop with @nickgilligan. Working on using my legs + feet.🦵🏽
Have you laughed today? 🙂
Grooving. 😛 @andrewhaydenkang @charleschentv
To the one that holds me DOWN!!! ❤️ Not literally. I mean the Urban Dictionary way. Lol.

My mom at her first company (she’s in the middle wearing the scarf). She had business partners - 6 other men. She was equally, if not more, competent than all of them and still they gave her no shares. The shares went to her husband (my dad) instead.
⠀
I’ve watched her build two Biotech companies in Silicon Valley. She often says, “the business gene, you either have it or you don’t.”
⠀
Hunger, seeing opportunities, clear decision making, having a sense of what other people need, finding solutions, efficiency, knowing when to use logic and when to listen to your gut, playing the long game…
⠀
Whether inherited or learned, I am over the moon grateful I adopted this “business gene” from her.
⠀
I think about all the bullshit she had to deal with in order to pave the way for us (much luckier) younger generation women. Along with forever feeling grateful, I feel anger, and it fires me up. ❤️‍🔥
Pinched nerve in my lower back but still groovin. 👵🏼

What do you do to clear out your mind?  Clip from episode # 298 with former NFL player @bigjoe. We talk breathwork, meditation, ice baths, psychedelics, ecstatic dance, and a bunch of other hippie things, all while sipping on Chagaccinos. ✌🏽
⠀
#showupwithchristinechang #breathwork #meditationpractice
Why do they look at me the same? 🧐

While some of the guys I dated could have communicated better, it takes two to tango. Advice to women who stick around, hoping he’ll change: No amount of time together or convincing will change him. People can change, but everyone decides if and when, for themselves.
⠀
After my healing journey I became clear on one thing: I deserve someone who feels sure about me, because I feel sure about me (self worth, baby!). 😎 When I learned to say no to men who didn’t want a committed relationship (boundaries), I began to choose better, and met my husband shortly after.
⠀
If you like this dating advice, my book, “Show Up: Finding Love for Independent Women” is available on Amazon. ❤️
⠀
Clip from episode # 298 with @bigjoe. #showupwithchristinechang
I ❤️ being a woman. 🙂 #internationalwomensday
Women who have common goals. ❤️‍🔥🚀👭

My highlight of the evening at the @goldhouseco x @theacademy Oscar party was taking a bite of this custom Sprinkles cupcake. So fluffy, so fresh. Then I put it down for literally TEN seconds because I had to take a photo. When I turned around, some fucker stole it! My bitten cupcake. I was so mad. It brought back childhood resentment of people taking my shit without asking. 😂
If I look tired it’s because I am. But I love moving. Dance is my cardio.🙂 @reflectionstudios.la @lindseygaardsmoe
After a 100+ degree, 50% humidity yoga class taught by @edsbritton. Swipe.🔥

The productivity mindset is alive and well in me. Btw, my book “Show Up: Finding Love for Independent Women” is available on Amazon. 😂
⠀
Are you aware of your coping mechanisms? Are you accepting of them, or are there some things you would like to change?
⠀
Clip from episode # 297 with @neetabhushan. #showupwithchristinechang

Do you respect when other people carve out time for you? Do you mindfully manage your time or are you chronically late?
⠀
@kevin.kreider & I are on the same page when it comes to time. If it’s a bbq and a bunch of people are rolling in and out, then yes - time doesn’t really matter. But when people carve out time specifically for you, and you are chronically late, or cancel last minute like it’s no biggie, or don’t show up with no effort of a heads up… Oof. Bad etiquette.
⠀
The most common excuse I hear is, “Some people aren’t good at managing their time!” In which I respond: If you are able to get to work on time, then it’s possible. You respect work, because otherwise you know you will get fired.
⠀
#isaidwhatisaid

Want to have fun dating instead of being anxious about it? 😭 It really comes down to self love, self worth, and getting clear. In my book I provide a roadmap to get there. Meep meep! 🚗 “Show Up: Finding Love for Independent Women” is available on Amazon.

Have you been through an identity crisis? 🫠 @createthelove & I talk all about navigating life transitions, finding your purpose, and living your truth. ❤️‍🔥
⠀
Clip from Episode # 271 of the Mark Groves Podcast.

When something calls your soul, do you listen? I was initially afraid to write my book, “Show Up: Finding Love for Independent Women” because it meant being seen. With my work as a photographer (@christinechangphoto), criticism didn’t bother me. If someone didn’t like my photography, I never felt like it was ME that they didn’t like.
⠀
Upon sharing experiences involving my personal life, it felt vulnerable. It’s my face. My voice. My experiences of pain, shame, and healing. But I KNEW it could help other women, and it reached a point where the idea couldn’t stay dormant in me anymore.
⠀
When something calls your soul, do you listen?
⠀
Clip from episode 271 of the Mark Groves podcast. ❤️ @createthelove

Use code CHRISTINECHANG for $15 off, or 15% off your entire order by using the link in my bio. My favorite flavor is the Daybreaker, with smooth and creamy Cacao.

New sex vs. married sex. 💦 The novelty of sex changes over time. In a healthy relationship, the emotional intimacy increases over time, but you can’t pretend to be seeing the same person for the first time after 10, 20, 30 years. Maybe a handful of times through personal growth or drugs 😂 but in general, it’s different.
⠀
@kelseychittick talks sex and dating again after losing her husband of twenty years. Clip from episode 300: “How To Love Life Again In Your Forties.”
⠀
#showupwithchristinechang

The older I get, the more particular of how I spend my energy. Really felt like hermitting this year for my bday but saw a few friends last minute for bruuunch.
⠀
I think about what constitutes the people I enjoy being around most. Calm, chill, grounded, accepting. You can hang without second guessing what you say, how you have to be, or how the other person will take it. A natural relaxed flow.
⠀
I think this energy is what most people ultimately wish for in intimate relationships. That you can just be you, and it’s enough. #41
Have you outgrown people in your life? Unsure what to do about it? @kelseydchittick & I talk adult friendships. Clip from episode 300. #showupwithchristinechang

Had a long layover at SFO on my way to Europe so mom picked me up to have dim sum. She handed me a canvas bag that had cuties 🍊, tissues, masks, and some Euros from her last trip. 🥹 Ngl, my parents have been driving me nuts lately. My triggers have been on fire. Lol. Remember that if you have people in your life who show up and care (despite annoying tendencies), be grateful. Also, everyone is dealing with their own shit, so be forgiving, including to yourself.✌🏽Love you ma.
Trips with girlfriends hit different. @shiningluvsmile @festivaldecannes

First time at Cannes. @festivaldecannes
⠀
The red carpet is funny. It can look glamorous from highlight clips, but in real life it’s a lot less romantic. People in line with their teams, egos, everything orchestrated to create a specific image. Completely made up.
⠀
Still I love it. 🤣 Give me all the gowns and photos.

It’s AAPI Heritage month and I couldn’t be more proud. Proud to have peers that exude excellence and create amazing things in this world.
⠀
If “you are the average of who you surround yourself with,” I think I’m doing just fine. 🏆

Independent ladies who are looking for a relationship with an amazing man: they are out there! For a long time I couldn’t “see them.” Now I see them all over the place! You may have to do some work on yourself if there are patterns you want to change: healing + self-awareness. I talk about how in my book, “Show Up: Finding Love for Independent Women,” available on Amazon. ❤️
Calm nervous system. ❤️

Women spend tens of thousands of dollars to “look good.” Where is the line for you? 🧐 I talk beauty & aging with Comedian @shiningluvsmile on the “Not Your Asian Women” podcast. Episode 2. Available on YT.

Both our husbands said the same thing. When asked, “Do you mind if I go on this trip without you?,” they both answered similarly: “It doesn’t matter what I say, because you’re going to do whatever you want to do. I know who I signed up for.” 🤣
⠀
Travel was one of the reasons Pete said he was attracted to me. “Because you are confident in knowing how to make yourself happy,” he said.
⠀
Tee hee. 🤗 On the real tho - this is why I say it’s important to show people who you are from the start. The person will accept you or they won’t. If a guy didn’t like that I traveled a lot, he’s not for me.
⠀
This is also why I fully support Pete religiously doing the things that light him up (soccer, the boys). It’s incredibly important to feel free and do things that fill your cup. From my experience, that’s when you show up to relationship best - when you feel like you can be you. 🥰
Do you use photo filters? 😂 @shiningluvsmile & I talk beauty and aging. Episode 2 of the “Not Your Asian Women” podcast. Available on YouTube.

Did your mom every criticize how you look? How has that impacted you? I personally am turning into my own version of my mom. 🐲👋🏽 Overly caring how I look was never super important to me. I’m more like my dad - he’s the CEO of a company and rocks sweats to work everyday. Day to day, there’s just so many other things I’d rather spend time on. HOWEVER, when it’s time to put yourself together, DO IT. 👑
⠀
Clip for episode 3 of the “Not Your Asian Women” podcast. We talk all about healing our relationship with our parents. Available on YouTube.
Date night at @the_macallan tasting. 🥃 Out of all alcohol I only appreciate the taste of whiskey and beer. Maybe I was a burly man in a previous life.

The Asian guilt trip is real. 🤡 @shiningluvsmile & I talk about getting clear and healing our relationship with our parents. Clip from episode 3 of the “Not Your Asian Women” podcast. Available on YT.

Opening night @tribeca. 🎥 We watched “Kiss the Future,” a documentary about an underground community in Sarajevo that kept hope alive during the Bosnian War with the help of U2 and journalist Bill Carter. The lessons are 💯 applicable to what’s going on in today’s political climate. Worth a watch if you care, or simply if you love U2.
Is it racism, or ignorance? 🤔 We talk all about racism on episode 4 of the “Not Your Asian Women” podcast. Available on YT. 🫶🏽 @shiningluvsmile

We both forgot it’s our wedding anniversary today. Pete’s calendar dinged him and then he told me. Lol. Honestly, the day we met is more meaningful to us than the day we had a party. Also, we’re not really the type to keep track of length. How we feel together is more important than how long. And I think THAT, is worth celebrating. We made dinner resy for tomorrow. 😘

My mom brought my sis & I to Disneyland a lot growing up and it’s one of the reasons we love it so much. I thought it was generous of her and then eventually learned that she did it to take breaks from my dad + her in laws.😂
‌
This is the first girls trip she’s taken to Disney with her granddaughter. Mom hung all day, walking fast and riding all the rides with us (including Guardians of the Galaxy)!
‌
She’s a trooper and I’m happy to see her energetic, curious, and happy! It was a great day (I only got triggered once). Lol.
‌
If it is available for you, spend time with your mother. ❤️

Had the most happy, heartbreaking, tiring, fulfilling experience of my life volunteering with @fosterlove at Disneyland. When siblings enter the foster system, the majority are put into different homes. This was a day for them to have fun, be kids, and reunite with siblings. ❤️
‌

Making friends is like dating. 💞 Clip from episode 13 of the “Not Your Asian Women” podcast. We talk all about how to make friends as an adult!
Scaring myself.

From my experience, your friend groups are like your family when you’re younger, with the majority of time spent with your crew. When people start marrying, having kids, or deciding to prioritize career, naturally the dynamics change.
‌
Saw some old friends over the weekend. Some of us haven’t seen each other in years! We talked about where we’ve been, grieving and acknowledging the changing dynamics. Things aren’t going to be exactly what they used to. Life grows, and it goes. Love each other and roll with it, while enjoying some R&B. 🥰

If there is one thing I would love to mentor young women, it is to know your worth. Do not tolerate disrespect. Do whatever you need to in order to feel empowered (i.e. community, skills, money). YOU HAVE CHOICE.

An intruder walked into my dad’s office this morning at 9:30am in Burlingame, California WHILE EMPLOYEES WERE INSIDE, and stole someone’s wallet. People were on calls and didn’t see him.

The front doors have a fob system but it happened to not latch that morning. Surveillance caught him looking into cars before entering the building. 

CA has turned into a shit show. The most infuriating part to me is how entitled people feel to leisurely commit crime. I don’t believe in having empathy for criminals. You break the law, you have repercussions.

CREEPY FOLLOWERS - do they bother you? @shiningluvsmile and I have very different takes on this. To me, if it’s not something I would like happening in real life, I don’t allow it on my social media either.
